description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and suitably experienced chief Cardiac Physiologists to join our friendly team. The Department provide a wide range of diagnostic and invasive cardiac investigations as well as provide pacemaker service. This post will mainly be for an experienced echocardiographer. Applicant should hold BSc in Clinical Physiology degree or equivalent and also have been accredited in in BSE/ASE/EACVI in transthoracic echocardiography.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts have been designed to help with the expansion of the Echo department with the introduction of the new stress echo service, along with the plans to start a physiologist led valve clinic with the final aim being the BSE Departmental Accreditation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department is working towards 7 day working, the successful applicant is expected to participate in this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;H Ahmet- Senior Chief Cardiac Physiologist/Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Huseyin.ahmet@bedfordhospital.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01234 792047&lt;/p&gt;
